<Layout title="I'm Angry At Both — The Govt That Leaked NEET And The CJP That Used Us For FCRA | Vipul Zope" locked={false}>
  <div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto px-6 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <h1 class="font-serif font-semibold text-[2rem] leading-[1.15] text-[var(--color-ink)] mb-2">i'm angry at both</h1>
    <p class="text-[1rem] leading-[1.5] text-[var(--color-ink-secondary)] mb-6">the govt that leaked NEET and the CJP that used us for FCRA</p>
    <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[var(--color-ink-muted)] mb-10">20 Jul 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-[0.95rem] leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-ink-secondary)]">
      <p class="font-serif text-[1.3rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] leading-[1.3]">the real timeline: NEET was the poster, FCRA was the agenda</p>
      <p class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-[0.08em] text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase">this is not a student movement. this is a FCRA negotiation using student crowd.</p>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-border)] my-6">

      <p class="font-serif text-[1.2rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">1. FCRA root — the real case</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">2007 onward:</strong> As per local reports, Leh administration allegedly flagged misuse of foreign funds.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">2020-21:</strong> As per audit note accessed via sources, 5 transactions were allegedly flagged — bus sale cash in foreign account, local volunteer money in foreign account, Sweden money for sovereignty study, return of foreign money, food fee cut.</p>

      <p>Wangchuk wants his foreign funding license back.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Aug 20, 2025:</strong> As per notice shared by sources, show cause notice issued.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Sep 25, 2025:</strong> As per sources, FCRA licence cancelled. CBI inquiry reportedly started on HIAL.</p>

      <p>Convicted? No. Only licence cancelled. But funding dead.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Mar 25, 2026:</strong> FCRA Amendment Bill reported to be listed — as per our tracking, it proposes seizure of assets if FCRA lapses. This Bill is reported to be listed for Monsoon Session starting 20 July. This is what Wangchuk wants to negotiate, in our view.</p>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-border)] my-6">

      <p class="font-serif text-[1.2rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">2. NEET leak — govt fails, then fixes</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">May 3, 2026:</strong> NEET 2026 leaks via NTA insider. Govt incompetent, true. Yes, this govt is incompetent — it leaked NEET and wasted our year.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">May 12, 2026:</strong> NEET cancelled, handed to CBI. Govt puts full focus on re-NEET.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">June 21, 2026:</strong> Re-NEET done with max security — mock drills, enhanced surveillance, 22 lakh appeared. Leak fixed.</p>

      <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] text-[0.95rem]">June 21 — July 16 — the real govt process window:</p>

      <p>After re-NEET, Secretary + NTA DG + Ministry need detailed committees, rewrite SOPs, vendor rules, shift OMR to CBT, Cabinet approval. As per standard procedure, it takes 3-4 weeks. File was moving since May 12, as per procedure. That is why result took till July 16. Logical.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">July 16, 2026:</strong> NEET UG 2026 Result declared — As per NTA result portal on that date.</p>

      <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] text-[0.95rem]">July 16 — July 20 — the 4-day window you caught:</p>

      <p>Result came July 16. Immediately after, result challenge window opens. Some students submitted alleged fake AI-generated OMR sheets. NTA warned legal action. Small student-level fraud, not leak in our assessment.</p>

      <p class="text-[var(--color-ink)] font-medium bg-[var(--color-accent-faint)] p-4 rounded-md border-l-3 border-[var(--color-accent)]">CJP play: They waited for July 16 result. They knew Day 1 Parliament July 20 is in 4 days where FCRA Bill is reportedly listed. So they shouted July 16-19 "See, still lapses, govt doing nothing." Then when govt announces SOPs/CBT reforms already under process since May 12, Wangchuk + Abhijeet went live July 20-22 — "We won, our hunger strike forced govt." In our view, students were used for reel.</p>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-border)] my-6">

      <p class="font-serif text-[1.2rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">3. Acting + Pradhan drama</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">May 15:</strong> CJI's remark during fake degree hearing was widely reported as cockroach analogy. Later clarified as not to be taken sentimentally. CJP made it a brand.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">May 16:</strong> CJP Instagram page was created by Abhijeet Dipke — self-described ex-AAP social media volunteer, PR student Boston as per his bio. Google Form party.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">May 17 — July 16:</strong> Instagram claims 10M-20M followers as per their page vs our ground count of maximum 2k at Jantar Mantar including media. Online hype.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">June 28:</strong> Hunger strike narrative — Police shifted him to hospital, family sought private hospital, court observed not detained. In our view, pure narrative acting through hunger strike.</p>

      <p>Cabinet rumour: Buzz that reshuffle due, Pradhan may be moved. No official order found till July 20. CJP made primary demand "Resignation of Pradhan" using that rumour.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">July 9:</strong> CJP announced Chalo Sansad on July 20.</p>

      <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">July 20 Today:</strong> Day 1 of Monsoon Session — reported to run 20 July to 13 Aug, with 7 Bills reportedly including FCRA Bill as per sources. You don't march on Day 1 for an exam already done. In our view, you march on Day 1 to negotiate FCRA.</p>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-border)] my-6">

      <p class="font-serif text-[1.2rem] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)]">4. Support — fact checked</p>

      <p>No official party resolution backing CJP found on official handles of Congress, BJP, AAP, TMC till July 20. Only individual leaders extended support — Mahua Moitra, Kirti Azad, Akhilesh Yadav, Brinda Karat, Manish Sisodia, Prakash Raj as per their posts. All photo-op, in our view.</p>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-border)] my-6">

      <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg-deep)] p-5 rounded-md border-l-3 border-[var(--color-accent)]">
        <p class="text-[var(--color-ink)] font-semibold mb-2">final corrected dot in one line:</p>
        <p>Re-NEET June 21 fixed leak &rarr; Result July 16 &rarr; Only 4 days gap to Day 1 Parliament &rarr; Use alleged AI OMR result frauds to keep anger alive &rarr; March July 20 to bargain FCRA + claim upcoming SOPs as your win.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">Yes, this govt is incompetent — it leaked NEET and wasted our year. But in our view, Wangchuk, Abhijeet and CJP are fraud — they knew govt fixed re-NEET with max security and needs weeks for SOPs, they knew FCRA Bill is reported on 20 July, so they used our anger, our AI OMR small lapses, our Pradhan anger, their hunger strike acting, to build a crowd for their FCRA negotiation. And they will frame govt's already-decided reforms as their win.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
